1
00:01:01.094 --> 00:01:08.569
With tensions rising over the protracted suspension of the National Assembly..

2
00:01:12.172 --> 00:01:23.817
It’ll be decided after tomorrow’s ruling-opposition summit. What a pathetic bunch..

3
00:01:23.884 --> 00:01:30.090
Have they no shame in wasting taxpayers’ money? The proposed presidential pardon is stirring things up.

4
00:01:30.123 --> 00:01:31.625
How come it’s in the papers before anything’s even been decided?

5
00:01:54.648 --> 00:02:05.626
“If I win, I’ll make all the donations”. I don’t have long left in my tenure. Do I have to attend all these events?

6
00:02:06.226 --> 00:02:51.405
Would you look at that? A President marking lottery numbers.. Pathetic! I’ll make a note of that, sir. President Kim wished success in hosting the World Cup and for happiness of fellow Koreans.. This is good. I made it spicier than usual. I thought you had a quite a few drinks at dinner last night. Russians love a drink, don’t they? Maybe this is why they tried to change the law. To enjoy the tasty foods for longer. Dictators must have had the best chefs.

7
00:03:24.571 --> 00:03:35.582
Do they expect me to do their job for the entire year? Cha is not an easy man. It won’t hurt to be prepared.

8
00:03:35.649 --> 00:03:41.221
What’s on tonight’s agenda? The presidential pardon, sir. We advise you to reconsider.

9
00:03:48.695 --> 00:04:11.084
personal forgiveness. The nation and our recent history isn’t ready to forgive them. Moreover, there is the outstanding issue of an unaccounted-for slush fund. The public sentiment remains strong. You might take the fall for your generosity. What are your thoughts, Minister?

10
00:04:11.151 --> 00:04:43.617
Do you think I’m going over the line, too? I was the chief justice for the case. They were tried as former Presidents and there was huge pressure. But, be it death penalty or life imprisonment. Sentencing them was only possible because the public approved. I believe you should approach this issue from that perspective.

11
00:04:44.451 --> 00:04:54.328
I’m the President of this country. A special pardon is the President’s right under the Constitution. Am I mistaken? No, it’s not unlawful, sir.

12
00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:21.855
What’s all that? I have a big presentation at the seminar. Couldn’t you have gotten a cab? Why spend money on a cab?

13
00:05:23.090 --> 00:05:28.495
This car was given to me for official duty not for picking up husbands. All right, all right..

14
00:05:31.965 --> 00:05:44.144
Take the presidential pardon for instance.. Would it have been possible earlier in his tenure? We’re dancing around the same topic. Let’s not distort his good intentions. -Turn up the volume, please? -Yes, ma’am.

15
00:05:44.244 --> 00:06:40.234
The current President was persecuted by the military government. In other words, he was the biggest victim. Why would he want to do this? To fulfill one of this government’s greatest objectives - to unite the nation. What about the slush fund? Please approach the subject more logically. Please let me speak.. We deeply regret that, too. It’s up to the judiciary bodies to investigate the matter fully. But, how do you expect the justice department to do a proper job when the government is clearly lacking the will. Are you accusing us of undermining the principles of division of powers? In this day and age? What’s the point of convicting and sentencing them to life in prison when they are let off right away? What’s the point of giving them the death penalty, only to free them after a year and a half? It was 2 years. Get your facts right. It was 20 months to be precise!

16
00:06:48.842 --> 00:06:55.349
How have you been, sir? You look more handsome than ever. They’re referring to you as the JFK of Korea.

17
00:06:55.415 --> 00:06:57.050
That must be an exaggeration, surely.

18
00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:21.175
Shall we get a beer? Excuse me? Isn’t it a bit early? Don’t be shy, young man.

19
00:07:25.946 --> 00:07:27.981
Come and sit over here.

20
00:07:41.628 --> 00:07:43.964
Let’s pass this one.

21
00:07:49.536 --> 00:08:05.485
All bills are important. Instead, I’ll let you have this one.. the revised Civil Service Law. We can’t be sloppy with these. It’s urgent, son. We gotta make decisions fast so that people can get on with their lives.

22
00:08:06.787 --> 00:08:08.622
Will you stop calling me “son”?

23
00:08:09.389 --> 00:08:11.491
You know how many times I changed your dirty diapers?

24
00:08:11.558 --> 00:08:18.031
All right, all right. Let’s move on. You have always been so illogical.

25
00:08:33.614 --> 00:08:36.884
E-yeon is coming back from school this year.

26
00:08:46.159 --> 00:08:49.396
So, what? Just letting you know.

27
00:08:51.431 --> 00:08:54.534
She’s well over thirty and still studying?

28
00:09:00.674 --> 00:09:02.276
That’s what I’m talking about.

29
00:09:15.522 --> 00:09:40.147
Are you trying to scare me with a stare? Guard! Did she say that? That I dated her? Your father did! That you were chasing after her. That’s just ridiculous! Study was my only focus. I can get the NIS to look into it. Don’t lie to me. I can’t believe this.

30
00:09:40.214 --> 00:09:43.283
You would use the agency’s service for personal reasons? Do you know what year we’re living in?

31
00:09:43.784 --> 00:09:53.894
That would call for impeachment. Hey. This one.. the Capital Administration Bill. Let me have it. What do you mean let you have it?! I shouldn’t have come by myself.

32
00:10:10.310 --> 00:10:36.770
It went very well. Although we didn’t manage to go over all outstanding bills. But, we had umm.. better results than initially anticipated from the marathon meeting.

33
00:10:42.042 --> 00:11:04.031
Forgive me for telling you this in a letter. found out why my family disapproved of us so ardently. Honey, come and watch this Mimi dies tonight. They still don’t know that they have the same father? They know now.

34
00:11:09.970 --> 00:11:23.183
I’m your host of tonight’s draw, Lucky Bae! We’re coming to you live with the first draw of the World Cup Lottery.. Has the battery run out? We’ll start the draw right away.

35
00:11:25.652 --> 00:11:38.732
Spin the balls! The numbers have to be in the order they appear on your screen. Ladies and gentlemen, the first lucky number is.. 6!

36
00:11:46.540 --> 00:12:13.333
Why your eyes look like mine, why your fingers look like mine, I’ll tell you now. The third number is.. It’s “0”! The fourth lucky number is.. 2! With two numbers remaining.. The fifth lucky number is.. 1!

37
00:12:21.842 --> 00:13:06.153
-And, the last number that will determine tonight’s lucky winner.. My mother who passed away when I was young, is your mother. Who will be the lucky winner of 24.4 billion Won? Mimi, you’re my sister! It’s number “9”!

38
00:13:11.825 --> 00:14:08.982
an ambulance entered the Blue House around 9 o’clock this evening and rushed directly to SNU Hospital. President Kim is reported to have no particular health conditions other than slightly high blood pressure and angina. It is suspected that stress from the marathon meeting earlier may have been the cause. How did it happen? He was watching a soap opera before he collapsed. A soap opera? Why would the President collapse over Mimi finding her father? The President is taking a rest after suffering from dizziness. The 4 leaders of the opposition and ruling party are convening an emergency meeting. Also, the Blue House will proceed with firm countermeasures against any press or individuals who circulate malignant rumors.. The Army will be fully prepared for any potential enemy attacks..

39
00:14:09.983 --> 00:14:16.557
It’s very fortunate that he didn’t suffer a concussion.

40
00:15:06.773 --> 00:15:13.113
..this drama series is so addictive.

41
00:15:17.651 --> 00:15:21.755
We have a car ready for you in the basement car park. It’s crowded with reporters outside.

42
00:15:22.923 --> 00:15:25.092
Thank you. This way, ma’am.

43
00:16:25.986 --> 00:16:31.525
Can you hear me, honey? Honey!

44
00:16:33.327 --> 00:16:36.597
Can you hear me, sir?

45
00:17:23.877 --> 00:17:27.548
He wants his wallet!!!

46
00:17:31.552 --> 00:17:57.311
at 8:30 this morning and asked for his wallet as the first thing. The President opened the wallet with trembling hands and looked at the old photograph of himself and the First Lady in tears, according to an aide present at the scene. President Kim is a true family man who thought of his family first, in the face of imminent death.

47
00:17:58.979 --> 00:18:00.747
We’re lucky to have him as our President.

48
00:18:42.389 --> 00:19:07.347
And, goal!!!!! Korea wins the match! Ladies and gentlemen, tonight’s match, truly an unscripted drama, ends with a spectacular last-minute goal from Ahn!

49
00:19:22.262 --> 00:19:28.202
They told me you stayed up by my bedside. What’s with the fuss? You mustn’t stay out all night being a single dad.

50
00:19:29.436 --> 00:19:34.408
It’s not like I didn’t have a place to crash. I was worried about you.

51
00:19:35.175 --> 00:19:36.743
You owe me a drink.

52
00:19:37.344 --> 00:19:50.424
How come? I collapsed at a perfect time for you. Because of what happened, the public will want a young and healthy President. Give it your best shot in the upcoming election.

53
00:19:50.490 --> 00:19:53.327
You may not have wisdom but you have a good health.

54
00:20:03.303 --> 00:20:27.227
House, 3 billion. Wife.. 2 and for daughter.. 1? Travel.. 0.5.

55
00:20:28.362 --> 00:20:43.710
No.. 1 is more like it. I think it’s best for you to take a few more days off. This might be too much of a strain right now. There’s no need to clear the schedule. I’m good. No need to worry.

56
00:20:51.818 --> 00:20:59.259
It’s a made-to-order model equipped with tons of high-tech devices. About 1 billion Won? Rather pricey.

57
00:21:00.460 --> 00:21:09.670
Will they give it to me when I step down? It’s for the use of the President only. But, you’ll be provided with another vehicle.

58
00:21:10.437 --> 00:21:17.311
They’re being cheap. In that case, I’ll just buy one for myself. Car.. 1 billion.

59
00:21:34.995 --> 00:21:56.049
When is 6 months from now? 6 months from now is.. February. Precisely, it’s two days before the Inauguration ..MUST BE CLAIMED AT THE DESIGNATED BANK WITHIN 6 MONTHS..

60
00:21:57.417 --> 00:22:12.366
If I won the lottery, I would make donations, in fact, I’ll spend it all on my fellow Koreans.

61
00:22:29.049 --> 00:22:42.029
We should have made him change his schedule. Why can’t you take it easy like other retiring Presidents? You’ll end up in the national cemetery before the Inauguration.

62
00:23:00.681 --> 00:23:14.761
For the purpose of improving the national brand of Korea, it’ll be imperative to allocate the extra budget funds and resources required for updating the system.

63
00:23:15.596 --> 00:23:19.666
And, of course..

64
00:23:47.528 --> 00:23:58.472
By providing training programs and educational literature for the tourism sector, and attracting fluent speakers of foreign languages.. Daddy!

65
00:25:11.345 --> 00:26:09.803
Please take a number slip, sir. Well, actually.. I’m here for the lottery.. In any case, take a number slip and wait for your turn, sir. Don’t jump the line, old man! But, I’m here for the lottery.. If you want to buy a lotto ticket, go to a corner shop. In the bank, you should take a slip.. Well, I need help with the vault. If you want to rob the vault you should come at night. If you want to do it during office hours get yourself a number slip! Is that so hard, old man? How dare you talk to me like that? I won the lottery and. I’m here to collect my money! What do you take me for, brat! Don’t you know who I am? Don’t you yell at me! Hey, old man! Suppose.. Even if you were the President of this country. You still gotta take a number slip and wait for your turn! Wait to be called for service..

66
00:26:10.037 --> 00:26:14.842
Sweet mother of Jesus!! Mr. President!

67
00:26:16.443 --> 00:26:23.750
Mr. President has won the lottery! Manager, bring out his money! Yes, sir! Security, escort him, now!

68
00:26:23.817 --> 00:26:28.355
Everyone, Mr. President has won the lottery!

69
00:26:39.266 --> 00:26:41.201
I can’t go there myself.

70
00:26:43.904 --> 00:26:46.807
Everybody knows who she is.

71
00:27:09.096 --> 00:27:11.565
the moment he collects the money.

72
00:27:35.689 --> 00:27:46.166
It’s not a crime for a President to win the lottery! You’re a citizen the same as anyone else. I am, right? You said you’d donate it all to a good cause. You gave your word.

73
00:27:47.034 --> 00:27:50.838
It’s always the mouth! You can always take it back.

74
00:27:51.471 --> 00:28:05.719
It’s natural for a politician to change his mind. You have a point. Everything you stood for and the integrity of your government will go down the drain. Give up the money. But, it’s 24 billion Won.

75
00:28:07.955 --> 00:28:23.036
20-what? Why didn’t you tell me earlier? What’s there to think about? Just eat dirt and take the money! 24 billion? Man.. I had no idea!

76
00:28:38.352 --> 00:28:47.227
I’ll sleep on the plane tomorrow. You have to go back so soon? I’ll be back for good, next year.

77
00:28:48.795 --> 00:28:52.466
Is there anything you need? Are you short of money?

78
00:28:54.134 --> 00:29:02.109
The collapse must have hurt you somehow. Is it funny that I talk about money?

79
00:29:06.046 --> 00:29:13.453
Can I take this? It’s my favorite picture. It was the hard times.

80
00:29:14.388 --> 00:29:32.940
I was constantly on the run or imprisoned for political reasons. I was never able to pay your tuition. You were always an easy target. Ji-wook’s father never got caught even if he was with you all the time.

81
00:29:33.774 --> 00:29:37.211
That’s because he backed out at all the critical moments.

82
00:29:41.114 --> 00:29:55.794
On the day I arrived. I saw Ji-wook at the hospital. He hasn’t changed a bit. He is just as stubborn as his old man. Do you want to see him? Pardon?

83
00:29:56.463 --> 00:30:00.100
No, why would I? I’ll get some sleep.

84
00:30:11.378 --> 00:30:14.848
You boys are dead ‘cuz this round is mine!

85
00:30:23.056 --> 00:30:31.265
Chef Jang, do we have some soju? I’m not sure if it’s okay to drink, sir. You only just got out of the hospital.

86
00:30:32.032 --> 00:30:36.637
Have a drink. No, sir.. Thank you.

87
00:30:43.443 --> 00:30:57.057
No one.. We were just playing to kill time but I was about to win big when you came in. It was a double round.

88
00:30:57.524 --> 00:30:59.059
I don’t know the rules.

89
00:30:59.893 --> 00:31:02.062
Of course!

90
00:31:03.430 --> 00:31:12.539
Looking back at life, I’ve never had fun. Why would you think that?

91
00:31:17.010 --> 00:31:37.331
Suppose, one day, a ton of money fell out of sky. Pardon? Say, while you’re going your way about 20 billion Won fell on you from out of nowhere and no one knows about it because it was a quiet alley. What would you do?

92
00:31:41.068 --> 00:31:57.050
If that much money fell on me I would die. What? If that sort of money fell on me from the sky it would break my neck the moment it hit. It would kill most people on the spot.

93
00:31:57.084 --> 00:32:06.660
Even if you survived.. there’s no one around to help you. So, you’d probably die after a few painful minutes.

94
00:32:11.932 --> 00:32:24.711
You’re right. That’s what would happen. If money fell on you from the sky. You’d die without getting any help. Because there is no one around. That’s the right answer. “You die”.

95
00:32:31.318 --> 00:32:40.394
it is our duty and privilege to keep with the proud and noble beliefs of the patriotic martyrs.

96
00:32:42.095 --> 00:33:28.509
I sincerely ask you to understand and approve the decision that I and this government have made regarding the Independences Day special pardons of the two former Presidents. We must end the vicious circle of conflict rooted in political and geographical differences. We must unite in peace and work together for a better tomorrow. I believe today’s decision will mark the beginning of a triumphant new chapter.

97
00:33:34.147 --> 00:33:43.323
That was the end of the speech I prepared for today. But, I have another short announcement to make.

98
00:33:45.025 --> 00:34:12.252
Not long ago, there was a launch of a new sports lottery. Everyone at the event including myself, took part by entering. This isn’t part of a report on operations. But, I’ll make an honest confession before you all today. I won the jackpot.

99
00:34:21.962 --> 00:34:33.207
The winning numbers. 6, 8, 0, 2, 1, 9. It’s the date I proposed to my wife.

100
00:34:44.685 --> 00:35:15.549
24.4 billion. It’s the kind of money that I would never even dream about. I’ve decided to donate the prize money to a scholarship foundation to help less fortunate youngsters with their studies. I’ve never lived as a rich man. So, I lack ideas as to how to spend this money wisely.

101
00:35:16.116 --> 00:35:30.264
If my decision, which I believe to be the only right one, can help young people build their dreams, It’ll be my greatest joy. And, if I may add..

102
00:35:31.064 --> 00:35:45.145
If there is anyone among my predecessors who has money that doesn’t rightly belong to them. How about spending it on a good cause? Just my thought.

103
00:36:12.206 --> 00:36:17.744
I’m sorry I didn’t tell you earlier. Have you lost your mind?

104
00:36:18.445 --> 00:36:44.538
Huh? I mean that money.. Good Gracious! Couldn’t you have kept a half, at least? I’m at a loss for words! -Honey, I.. -Forget it! And, you proposed to me in March, not February. Was it? I’m sure it was February. Have you ever seen cherry blossoms in February?

105
00:36:48.742 --> 00:36:55.249
You’re right. It was during the blossom season. So, it was March.

106
00:36:58.919 --> 00:37:11.331
say that I want to keep the money? And, be a national laughing stock? I could say. I’ll keep the money and give up the pension. Can you not talk for a moment, Mr. President?

107
00:37:30.851 --> 00:37:52.940
I do solemnly swear that I will faithfully execute the Office of President of the Republic of Korea and will to the best of my ability, preserve, protect and defend the Constitution of the Republic of Korea. President of Republic of Korea, Cha Ji-wook.

108
00:38:15.562 --> 00:38:26.573
The initial detection was made at 21:00 by the Combined Forces Command and we received the report at 23:05. How come we are the last to know about tensions taking place in our waters.

109
00:38:28.542 --> 00:38:37.918
Maritime command is still in the hands of Pacific Command, sir. Mr. President, it’s the White House.

110
00:38:46.460 --> 00:38:50.430
Very slim, sir. Not even a little?

111
00:38:59.873 --> 00:39:12.319
Good morning Mr. President. I’m sorry but it’s nighttime, here. Shit! I forgot. I just received the report.

112
00:39:13.320 --> 00:39:15.556
Of course, hours later than you.

113
00:39:17.090 --> 00:39:40.881
We will be having an NSA meeting in a few hours and of course our conclusion will be reacting strongly against it. If congress approves, we will be moving our 7th fleet. Shouldn’t we think about the cause first? Pardon?

114
00:39:41.748 --> 00:39:53.360
Japan has moved their missile base to the Northwest to protect the trajectory. And in the name of training, they have focused their Maritime Force on North Korea and in our territorial waters.

115
00:39:54.127 --> 00:40:15.782
As you know, without prior consent from the concerning countries a military activity of this kind can be deemed an act of provocation. Japan would’ve anticipated this reaction. Don’t you think it’s weird that Japan is knowingly creating tension?

116
00:40:16.350 --> 00:40:19.920
We don't have time to think about such thing, Mr. President.

117
00:40:28.762 --> 00:40:44.044
but a military conflict. by all means, when congress approves, the Republic of Korea will have to open up both air space and its territorial waters.. According to the plan..

118
00:40:54.922 --> 00:41:05.966
enters our air and waters, then, so will the Japanese. Self-Defense Force, right? Be rational about this..

119
00:42:03.891 --> 00:42:25.112
We demanded the Japanese clear out by an official letter. In a worst case scenario, you should be prepared to get China involved. The simplest solution would be to convince North Korea. If they withdraw, we can untangle this problem. A more urgent issue at hand is the upcoming general election. You should really pay more attention.

120
00:42:26.213 --> 00:42:27.181
Approval ratings dropped again?

121
00:42:28.615 --> 00:42:29.416
Water, please?

122
00:42:30.617 --> 00:42:35.255
Diplomatic tension with Japan is creating unrest among the public.

123
00:42:36.156 --> 00:42:41.995
And, the party is grieving about the lack of support on your part. So..?

124
00:42:42.396 --> 00:42:47.935
Are you asking me to put on a show or something for ratings?

125
00:42:56.543 --> 00:43:02.580
Things are not looking good. We cannot afford to lose to the Opposition.

126
00:43:29.510 --> 00:43:40.187
the Korean government.. isn’t actively dealing with the recent episode.. of provocation by the North Korean military.

127
00:43:44.491 --> 00:44:07.047
You seem to be mistaken. I have summoned you here, Ambassador! Not for your opinion or a chit-chat, were triggered by Japan’s military action. Do you understand?

128
00:44:07.114 --> 00:44:24.765
But, it’s a.. legitimate.. Please speak in Japanese. You have a translator. Wouldn’t it be easier? Why sweat it? -Just speak in Japanese. -Should I go home? I’m sorry.

129
00:44:33.006 --> 00:44:43.483
Take a seat. This training was a legitimate military activity. We never violated foreign territories and acted under approval from the Pacific Command.

130
00:44:47.354 --> 00:44:50.757
Do you take me for an idiot?!

131
00:44:58.999 --> 00:45:32.366
The Maritime Force intruded into our waters 3 times while relocating to the northwest and the standoff area is conventionally prohibited from military activities. You know that, don’t you? This is not military training but a military action and it’s a natural reaction for North Korea which works in favor of your government. Because such military tension will raise concerns for national security and stirred-up public sentiment will pave the way for legislation of the. New National Security Law that the right wing government always wanted. Isn’t that so?

132
00:45:33.667 --> 00:45:40.073
What’s the matter? Lost for words? I’m so sorry but you spoke too fast..

133
00:45:40.140 --> 00:45:41.808
Don’t take the Korean government for a fool.

134
00:45:43.277 --> 00:45:47.848
We may have a humiliating history but we don’t do humiliating politics.

135
00:45:50.117 --> 00:45:52.486
We’d better wrap it up for today.

136
00:45:57.925 --> 00:46:04.231
Could you put the blind up? Thank you!

137
00:47:10.464 --> 00:47:28.248
The night view was spectacular with all the bright lights on bridges and buildings. I’m flattered. Thank you. Why would you be? It’s not like you built them.

138
00:47:32.252 --> 00:47:43.897
You cannot take an emotional approach with Japan. Because that’s what they want. They want to make an issue out of the current crisis.

139
00:47:50.170 --> 00:48:12.092
We’re telling them to stay out of our waters, telling them to stop pointing missiles at our country. In case they’re having wild ideas about our people again, we’re telling them we’re pissed off

140
00:48:12.159 --> 00:48:52.933
and that we won’t blankly stare like the Americans or the South Koreans. Are you saying you’re prepared to go war? Who are you? I’m the Chief of National Intelligence. But then, when you dropped a missile in Japanese waters or pressed on with plans to launch satellites, the surrounding countries passed over in silence. Because we wanted to prevent war, at all costs. And, you are..? I’m the Secretary of National Security. Did you invite me over to gang up on me? What do you mean gang up on you? Listen!

141
00:48:54.968 --> 00:49:13.554
It was the same back in ’94 and ’08 when the Americans pushed us over. We have never changed our position because we’re not Afghans playing with popguns in caves. Or some tiny banana republic in Africa or Central America that sprouts up and disappears.

142
00:49:19.026 --> 00:49:23.197
Are you scared of war, Mr. President?

143
00:49:38.278 --> 00:49:50.224
that I’m scared of. First is needles. Second is when my little son raises his hand with a question.

144
00:49:56.496 --> 00:49:57.764
candlelight vigils.

145
00:50:04.505 --> 00:50:05.739
We’ll go to war if it’s necessary.

146
00:50:13.714 --> 00:50:15.482
Now, you have to trust us.

147
00:50:16.450 --> 00:50:26.560
No, trust me, Cha Ji-wook. I’ll prove to you that a solid government and good politicians are stronger than a million troops.

148
00:50:33.901 --> 00:50:52.819
Han Kyung-ja, the former Minister of Law. She’s a good card. She could be a breath of fresh air temporarily. But, are we ready for a female president? A publicity stunt for the election, clearly. You think so?

149
00:50:55.489 --> 00:50:57.357
Why am I going to the market?

150
00:50:58.358 --> 00:51:12.372
To get a sense of public sentiment. I would like to thank my fellow candidates. Hang on.. That woman there..

151
00:51:14.708 --> 00:51:19.580
