it’s my husband, Choi Chang-myun.

330
01:39:44.885 --> 01:39:47.221
-Are you okay? -Yeah.

331
01:40:04.671 --> 01:40:12.006
I’m the presidential spouse, Choi Chang-myun. I’m sorry I’m late.

332
01:40:15.048 --> 01:40:20.988
Today is the birthday of my dear wife and our President.

333
01:40:23.891 --> 01:40:34.868
It should have been a day of happiness and celebration but because of me, it was one of the worst days in her life.

334
01:40:36.670 --> 01:40:51.051
I had a dream of retiring to a farm with my wife. So, I bought a small ranch with my life savings. I had no idea it would turn out to be such a disaster.

335
01:40:55.155 --> 01:40:59.760
I just sold off the land.

336
01:41:02.529 --> 01:41:34.661
Looking back, this wasn’t the first time. I failed to provide the support she needs for carrying out her duties as President. I regret so much only adding to her burdens. And, it makes me realize that I probably won’t change as a person.

337
01:41:35.596 --> 01:41:42.436
So, I made a small resolution and, felt I should announce it before I have a change of heart.

338
01:41:52.479 --> 01:42:05.592
I thought of you in the old days and I got choked up. You are as beautiful now as you have ever been.

339
01:42:31.285 --> 01:42:38.058
It’s not possible for me to be with you and live as a presidential spouse.

340
01:42:39.826 --> 01:42:42.329
What's going on? What did he say?

341
01:42:49.536 --> 01:42:50.671
I’m so sorry.

342
01:43:06.553 --> 01:43:12.025
It’s an emergency! A crisis! No, not a crisis either.

343
01:43:22.002 --> 01:43:48.695
For the first time in the history of Korea, a sitting President may get divorced during her presidential term. This afternoon’s statement by Professor Choi was his sole decision which he hopes, will allow the President to devote herself to her presidential duties. Lawyers for Democratic Society has volunteered to represent Professor Choi.. The public points finger of blame at the Opposition..

344
01:44:02.042 --> 01:44:10.517
It’s backfiring on us. Who did you hit, the President or her husband?

345
01:44:14.555 --> 01:44:43.684
This is an opportunity for us. A President with a family crisis! She’s as vulnerable as can be. Look at the survey results. Public reaction is contrary. They think we’re responsible for the President’s divorce. Don’t you know what she represents to the people? To the public, she’s the mother-, wife- and daughter-in-law figure. The Mother Mary, Korea’s Joan of Arc and Cleopatra..

346
01:44:46.753 --> 01:44:55.128
Maybe not the Cleopatra.. Is it not? Did I say Cleopatra? The point is..

347
01:44:56.296 --> 01:45:12.306
The opposition seems to be worried about taking the blame. Has she made up her mind about a divorce? “President sacrificing her marriage for the sake of her duties”.. Not bad.

348
01:45:12.980 --> 01:45:47.548
Professor Choi has been a ticking time-bomb. Maybe she’s better off without him. Have you ever been through a divorce? No, I’m happily married. I went through with it twice. When was the second time? The first time was not in the record. You think a divorce will allow you to focus better on your job? Who should be handling the matter anyway? The personnel affairs? How come? It goes under political affairs. What? Definitely not the foreign policy.

349
01:45:48.081 --> 01:45:53.253
Leave me out of this. How can you let this happen?

350
01:45:53.287 --> 01:45:57.057
You know what dad’s like! What about me?

351
01:45:58.058 --> 01:46:24.551
Are you blaming me for what he has done? But, you know how hard it has been for him. Before being one man’s wife, I’m the President of this country. How can I do my job if I have family troubles to worry about. If he can’t put up with it.. then, we have no choice. -Please mother.. -He started it all. Even if he comes back, things won’t change for the better.

352
01:46:25.352 --> 01:46:27.187
Suit yourself, Madam President.

353
01:46:32.593 --> 01:47:00.521
I loved him with all my heart. However, since taking office, I found loving someone as a private person a very difficult task. Today, I’m mustering up the courage to make an announcement about a decision I made.

354
01:47:03.690 --> 01:47:18.105
I decided to remain by myself as your President, not as a wife to a..

355
01:47:26.180 --> 01:47:51.905
What’s with the humiliating tone? Am I begging for sympathy for a poor divorcée? What’s with “tears” in brackets? You want me to cry here? Today, I stand before you as your President, not a wife to a man.. Like this?

356
01:47:53.540 --> 01:47:55.075
I’m sorry, ma’am.

357
01:47:55.642 --> 01:48:04.218
We’ve never dealt with this kind of situation.. Should the President present herself at the court for divorce?

358
01:48:04.751 --> 01:48:06.954
For formalities..

359
01:48:07.888 --> 01:48:24.505
And other things like alimony.. She is praised as the mother figure of the 21st century. And now, she’s fallen a victim of a political snare thanks to the Opposition.

360
01:48:24.938 --> 01:49:20.961
Although he claimed an innocent coincidence, he did buy land awaiting major development. Please, let’s use some common sense here. The President’s husband bought the land in his own name so that the world will know when he makes a huge profit out of it? A five-year-old would laugh at that. Well, he just did that laughable thing. Are you listening to what I’m saying? It’s not us that’s funny but the way you people think. Some claim that the President has made up her mind about the divorce. Nothing has been decided. Please be careful with the wording. Our society places great value on family, which is why the public is so concerned. They say “Cultivate body, order family then, make peace for the world”. People are concerned as to whether or not she’ll be able to carry out her duties without the support of a solid family behind her.

361
01:49:21.028 --> 01:49:30.604
It’s funny you should say that. The former President Cha was a wifeless father. Did he ever have solid family support behind him? A wifeless father?!

362
01:49:31.305 --> 01:49:41.715
Did you just refer to the former President as a “wifeless father?” Are you trying to insult the former head of state? What uneducated absurdity?

363
01:49:41.782 --> 01:50:15.349
How dare you talk to me like that? How old are you? Why are you asking me my age? We were in the same class in college. How old I am is how old you are! I failed my entrance exams twice. That’s fantastic! Well done for re-taking your exams! You must be really proud! Are you mocking me? You have just insulted the 200,000 students nationwide that are re-taking exams. What did I ever say about them? I’m talking about you! Take your words back this moment or I’ll see to it that you pay for it. I can’t and I won’t!! Make a public apology right this moment!

364
01:50:20.120 --> 01:50:27.294
No books or TV or talking on the phone while eating your dinner, okay?

365
01:50:47.714 --> 01:50:52.519
I hope I’m not interrupting you at a busy time.

366
01:50:52.553 --> 01:51:10.671
I have a favor to ask. Would you be willing to give a lecture for my students? I’ll check my schedule.

367
01:51:10.737 --> 01:51:28.689
This morning, the President invited her two predecessors, the former Presidents Kim and Cha, to a luncheon at the Blue House and discussed the main objectives and pending issues of her government.

368
01:52:00.554 --> 01:52:10.931
I studied politics at university like yourselves and served as the President until last year

369
01:52:13.233 --> 01:52:16.436
in case, some of you didn’t know.

370
01:52:20.040 --> 01:52:34.354
You parted with your wife quite early and served your term without the support of a First Lady. I think you might have hopes of meeting someone special again. Did you meet that special person during your tenure?

371
01:52:38.859 --> 01:52:43.263
That’s class A confidentiality.

372
01:52:48.168 --> 01:52:53.607
Tell us! Tell us!

373
01:53:01.315 --> 01:53:21.768
On many occasions, I felt lonely. Even if I had the best advisers and was surrounded by people who had faith in me. There were times I wanted to be in love again

374
01:53:23.537 --> 01:53:34.915
to have that special feeling for someone. But, I found that as a President, it’s difficult to love one person only.

375
01:53:40.554 --> 01:53:45.192
to love, cherish and respect one person.

376
01:53:48.962 --> 01:54:06.146
So, I gave it up. And now, I regret giving it up so much. I had lunch with President Han this afternoon. As you know,

377
01:54:07.247 --> 01:54:20.994
she is going through a tough time at the moment. I told her what I learned from my experience. To be President for one person when it comes to a certain moment.

378
01:54:27.935 --> 01:54:29.970
having regrets later on.

379
01:54:53.026 --> 01:54:54.795
Don’t flatter me.

380
01:54:56.797 --> 01:54:58.565
It’s getting chilly.

381
01:55:46.046 --> 01:55:48.482
It happens when I’m nervous.

382
01:56:45.539 --> 01:56:56.550
I haven’t cooked in years. Mr. Choi is a good cook. He made food here?

383
01:56:56.617 --> 01:57:11.765
Time to time, ma’am. On your birthday, it was Mr. Choi who made your birthday soup. So typical of him. How come you’re not married?

384
01:57:13.767 --> 01:57:31.952
My youngest is going to college this year. Excuse me! Why did I think you weren’t married.. Please forgive me. That’s okay. I get that from time to time.

385
01:57:40.227 --> 01:57:41.000
Pardon?

386
01:57:42.162 --> 01:57:44.131
How are things at home?

387
01:57:44.531 --> 01:57:51.805
I don’t go home much but still, it’s great.

388
01:57:56.276 --> 01:58:41.855
A President could make her people happy, even if she isn’t happy herself, couldn’t she? The President doesn’t necessarily have to be happy to make the lives of people better, right? I may be wrong but I believe.. just as a President wishes that all her people are happy, everyone wants their President to be happy. Not a single person would want the President to be miserable. You think so?

389
01:58:42.689 --> 01:59:02.409
That’s what people want. It would be nice if the President devoted herself to making the people happy but people who have a miserable President cannot be truly happy. Koreans are good people, A lot more so than you might think.

390
01:59:09.816 --> 01:59:18.392
I’m only a cook but I know that much.

391
01:59:27.968 --> 01:59:47.154
You know I had lunch with the two former Presidents. They both told me to pay a visit here, when faced with a dilemma that I cannot solve by myself. Now I can see what they meant. Thank you.

392
01:59:51.758 --> 01:59:56.697
Where can she be at this hour? She’s not at the Residence.

393
01:59:56.763 --> 01:59:57.898
Sir,

394
02:00:00.601 --> 02:00:04.738
I received a report that she just left the main gate. What are you talking about?

395
02:00:05.606 --> 02:00:06.907
Sir!

396
02:00:07.774 --> 02:00:09.009
The main gate!

397
02:00:09.176 --> 02:00:11.578
Right! The main gate!

398
02:00:11.678 --> 02:00:13.914
Don’t get in the way you idiots!

399
02:00:26.193 --> 02:00:33.467
Why did you let her pass by herself? Would she go grocery shopping at this hour, dumbass?

400
02:00:38.605 --> 02:00:39.606
Sorry, sir!

401
02:00:54.321 --> 02:01:16.476
disappear in the middle of the night? We were just chatting about happiness and other things.. While picking anchovy guts? What are you talking about? God, this is annoying! Turn on the GPS. Have a chopper locate the vehicle. It’s the Blue House.

402
02:01:17.110 --> 02:01:18.712
I’m the Chief of Security.

403
02:01:18.779 --> 02:01:20.747
We know where she is headed.

404
02:01:20.814 --> 02:01:38.565
Give them a call, too. Put me on! Chief Joo? This is the Chief of Personnel. Don’t have her pull over in the city. We can’t let anyone see her. Don’t let the press find out, no matter what! Escort her out of the city, okay?

405
02:02:15.202 --> 02:02:18.172
Where’s the next bottle neck point? An-sung Intersection, sir.

406
02:02:19.173 --> 02:02:23.477
Stop the vehicle before she enters the intersection. And, set up a road block in E7.

407
02:03:36.750 --> 02:03:41.855
I’m sorry but this is a personal matter. I assumed from the direction you were heading.

408
02:03:43.390 --> 02:03:47.060
It’s appropriate to use the official escort for this. Please let me take the wheel, ma’am.

409
02:03:47.995 --> 02:03:49.963
I don’t need an escort.

410
02:03:50.631 --> 02:03:59.106
I won’t be long. Your driver’s license has expired. Would you like me to call you a cab?

411
02:04:24.831 --> 02:04:28.302
Destination is Madam President’s in-laws’.

412
02:05:38.272 --> 02:05:40.607
You drove here. Why are you out of breath?

413
02:07:42.829 --> 02:07:44.364
Mind your own ticket.

414
02:07:44.765 --> 02:08:07.421
Let me see what you got. Don’t look at mine. Focus on yours. You have a lovely temper! “6” is a good number. Says who? I hope I win the jackpot this time. It’s not easy I know because I’ve done it before. You’ll give it all away again? I’ll keep it all for myself.

415
02:08:14.928 --> 02:08:48.529
People think that Presidents are special people. Of course, they are not wrong in thinking that. But, what we often forget is that at certain moments, they are someone’s husband, wife or parent. Their joy, sadness and happiness is not all that different from our own.

416
02:08:58.138 --> 02:09:13.820
If an old President comes over for a drinks, or a President who has given up smoking asks for a cigarette. In the early morning,

417
02:09:13.887 --> 02:09:25.758
when he greets you with hello we say to him with a big smile, “Good morning, President!”